Try executing this chunk by clicking the Run button within the chunk or by placing your cursor inside it and pressing Ctrl+Shift+Enter.

library(shiny)
library(haven)
library(tibble)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
Broadband <- read_dta("broadband_county_year.dta")
broad <- as_data_frame(Broadband)
broadband <- as_tibble(broad)
broadband
ggplot(broadband, aes(x=broadband)) + geom_histogram() +facet_wrap(~year) 

#boxplot showing percentiles
ggplot(broadband, aes(y= broadband)) + geom_boxplot()+facet_wrap(~year)


# How do the broadband percentages of different broadband percentiles (10th, 25th, 50th, 75th, 90th of broadband percentages) change over time?
q10 <- as.numeric(quantile(broadband$broadband, 0.10))
q25 <- as.numeric(quantile(broadband$broadband, 0.25))
q50 <- as.numeric(quantile(broadband$broadband, 0.50))
q75 <- as.numeric(quantile(broadband$broadband, 0.75))
q90 <- as.numeric(quantile(broadband$broadband, 0.90))
q100 <- max(broadband$broadband)
ggplot() + 
  geom_point(data = subset(broadband, broadband > 0 & broadband <= q10), aes(x = year,  y = broadband), color = "red") +
  geom_point(data = subset(broadband, broadband > q10 & broadband <= q25), aes(x = year, y = broadband), color = "green") +
  geom_point(data = subset(broadband, broadband > q25 & broadband <= q50), aes(x = year, y = broadband), color = "blue") +
  geom_point(data = subset(broadband, broadband > q50 & broadband <= q75), aes(x = year, y = broadband), color = "purple") +
  geom_point(data = subset(broadband, broadband > q75 & broadband <= q90), aes(x = year, y = broadband), color = "orange") +
  geom_point(data = subset(broadband, broadband > q90 & broadband <= q100), aes(x = year, y = broadband), color = "pink") 

#Create a histgram and boxplot distribution of broadband growth rates from 2006 to 2016
filtered_data <- broadband[, c("county", "year", "broadband")]

pivot_table <- pivot_wider(filtered_data, names_from = year, values_from = broadband)

pivot_table <- as_tibble(pivot_table)
pivot_table$broadband_growth = (pivot_table[[12]] - pivot_table[[2]])/(pivot_table[[2]])
ggplot(pivot_table, aes(x=broadband_growth)) + geom_histogram() 

ggplot(pivot_table, aes(y=broadband_growth)) + geom_boxplot() 

# how does a county's income affect the share of county with broadband (broadband percentage)?
ggplot(broadband, aes(x=income, y=broadband)) + geom_point() 

# how does a county's number of providers affect the share of county with broadband(broadband percentage)?
ggplot(broadband, aes(x=providers, y=broadband)) + geom_point()

# how does a county's minority population affect the share of county with broadband(broadband percentage)?
ggplot(broadband, aes(x=minority, y=broadband)) + geom_point()
